name: Deoxyribonucleic acid (DNA)
description:
Every normal human being has 43 chromosomes consisting of 23 pairs. Genetic clues are in a chemical compound called deoxyribonucleic acid (DNA) genetic influence on all innates determined by the special chemical content of the pair's genes in the form of the interaction of several corresponding genes.

In this work I use 43 movements that interact as many as 23 touches to display a suitable interaction and become a work that can be enjoyed coupled with music that makes the touch more intense to the audience.
